 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ublackwood.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Blackwood</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://members.aol.com/dcreelma/imagesite/animated/new/myskull.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <b>knows that Warriors are Superior</b><br>   <font color=#FF0000>(8/8/00 11:34:43 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/dcreelma/imagesite/animated/otherstuff/litning.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Dueling or PvP</span><hr size=1> Couple of suggestions...  From my experience, these are a few things I would do when dueling casting classes.<br>
<br>
1. If you are a large race, keep your slam skill maxxed, and use to interrupt spells.  If you are a mid-size race, get a shield (maybe just for dueling), and bash to interrupt.<br>
<br>
2. Get a bow, and keep your archery skill maxxed.  You can at least hit them (with the possibility of interrupting spells) while you are rooted.  This skill has other, useful applications (eg. pulling).<br>
<br>
3. Try to increase your save vs. magic resistance.  This may be a bit difficult - as gear is usually (in my experience) associated with resistances OR stats - not both.  So, you may want to carry MR gear for duels.<br>
<br>
If you play on a non-pvp server, you should not lose exp, nor will the opposing player be able to loot your equipment.  Make sure you bind somewhere close to where you are fighting - just in case.  I am unsure of the rules on pvp servers...<br>
<br>
